						               													<description>Ardennes Petite (Ardennes Small) is a very small-scale - only 6 hexes to Namur! - eight 2-day turn (16Dec44-2Jan45) division-to-corps-level Battle of the Bulge minigame, designed as a half-hour-lunch game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The U.S. starts with 6 units - the Germans with 9.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Combat is a fairly simple 1:2 to 4:1 Disruption/Retreat combat odds system, with no Defender Eliminated outright, except against 14th Cavalry Group, if it is defending alone.  Fortification for corps-level infantry units.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;German Pressed Attack and Waffen-SS Ruthlessness (and consequential GI Rage) rules.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;As you can see in Images, Patrick Tremoureux has his beautiful professional renditions of the map and counters.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
